summary: Diff implements major parts of the seller onboarding flow and seller dashboard UI, updates global theme tokens to an emerald-neutral palette, adds supplier->products navigation via URL filtering, and adds asset path constants and logo usage in the header. However, the required generated image files themselves are not evidenced in the diff, and some added features (admin seeding button, Stripe setup modal, placeholder migration) are not part of the BuildRequest.

missing_requirements.requirement: Add and use required static generated images under frontend/public/assets/generated (logo, hero banner, product placeholder) and reference them directly from the frontend.
missing_requirements.reason: The diff adds frontend/src/utils/assets.ts and references to these paths in UI, but does not show the actual image files being added under frontend/public/assets/generated.

hallucinated_features.description: Admin-only demo product seeding UI (AdminSeedButton) added to the app layout.
hallucinated_features.reason: BuildRequest does not request an admin seeding feature.

hallucinated_features.description: Admin-only Stripe configuration modal shown in the app (StripeSetupModal).
hallucinated_features.reason: BuildRequest focuses on redesign + seller onboarding/dashboard and does not request adding Stripe configuration UI.

hallucinated_features.description: Backend migration module stub added (backend/migration.mo) and wired into backend/main.mo.
hallucinated_features.reason: BuildRequest allows creating backend/migration.mo only if state shape changes require it; the diff evidence does not demonstrate an actual state transformation (stub returns old) or a clear state-shape change necessity.
BuildRequest does not request adding or updating a project tracking JSON file as part of the product changes.
